      <title>“The Citizen’s Card” and Orthodox Opposition in Greece: Part 2</title>
      <link>http://feeds.ancientfaith.com/~r/PostcardsFromGreece/~3/XzJSWozQVSc/the_citizens_card_and_orthodox_opposition_in_greece_part_2</link>
     <guid isPermaLink="false">http://ancientfaith.com/podcasts/postcards/the_citizens_card_and_orthodox_opposition_in_greece_part_2#10285</guid>
 <description>What is the Orthodox response to the new "citizen card" and the events and developments surrounding it? How should we live and what should be our stance vis-a-vis these "signs of the times"? It is an issue of personal religious freedom of conscience and a matter of confessing the Faith and the name of Christ. Listen as Fr. Peter relates the major points from a speech recently given to a large gathering in Thessaloniki by an Elder from Mount Athos, who is also one of the twenty abbots on Athos.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
